<p>The benefit of using the Sharpe ratio as the objective is that it maximizes returns while minimizing the return volatility. It's usually psychologically easier to keep a live algorithm deployed if it has minimal swings in equity than if it has large swings in equity. The drawback of using the Sharpe ratio is that it may limit your potential returns in favor of a less volatile equity curve.</p>
